<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The mhd_assert only checks that data is non-NULL when length>0, but an assertion macro is often compiled out. If mhd_assert is a no-op (e.g. in release builds) a caller could pass data == NULL with length > 0 and later memcpy calls (the one copying bytes_left and the final memcpy copying length bytes) will dereference data and access beyond bounds. Thus the single assertion is insufficient to guarantee no out‑of‑bounds accesses to the pointer parameters of the <string.h> functions.
</scenario>

